About

Design that thinks strategically

I'm a Product Designer and Design Strategist with over a decade of experience turning enterprise complexity into clarity. I specialize in making dense, technical systems feel intuitive ‚Äî whether that's an AI assistant for network engineers or a parliamentary app used by MPs across India.

My work spans Agentic AI, ERP/SAP platforms, banking workflows, government mobile apps, and industrial sensor dashboards ‚Äî always grounded in rigorous user research, behavioral design thinking, and clear business strategy.

At Vodafone VOIS, I lead design for Agentic AI and SAP-based enterprise applications, and I'm the design lead for NOVA ‚Äî an internal Gen AI knowledge portal and virtual assistant built for global network logistics teams.

Beyond the day job, I write about Service Design and Gamification on Medium, and actively mentor emerging designers on ADPList ‚Äî accumulating over 1,000 mentorship minutes and earning a Certificate of Appreciation for the community.

Deep Dive

Mindreader AI ‚Äî Case Study

01 ‚Äî Discover
Heuristics + Competitive Analysis

Conducted heuristic evaluation, expert review, UX interviews with sales professionals, and competitive analysis. Core finding: unclear messaging caused trust breakdown and immediate drop-off ‚Äî users saw the tool as "horoscope-like" rather than professional.

02 ‚Äî Define
Persona, Pain/Gain & IA

Defined the core persona: sales professionals in insurance and investment. Mapped pain/gain framework revealing the gap between perceived and actual utility. Redesigned IA around a dashboard-centric model with clear journeys from signup through analysis results.

03 ‚Äî Design
Trust-First Onboarding + Dashboard

Implemented trust-building onboarding before exposing analysis features. Redesigned analysis flow supporting multiple input methods: text, images, quizzes, or direct client-facing quiz links. Built a complete UI library and visual design system.

04 ‚Äî Deliver
Dev Handoff + Validation

Created "Design at a Glance" component docs for the dev team ‚Äî specifying dos and don'ts for headers, cards, CTAs, and more. Ran user testing to validate improved clarity, trust, and task completion.

Key Insights
  • Users couldn't identify the tool's value in the first session ‚Äî leading to abandonment before any analysis was attempted.
  • Multi-step analysis with ambiguous upload instructions was a critical learnability barrier. Users explicitly asked for "three simple steps."
  • AI skepticism required trust-building UX strategy ‚Äî not just cleaner UI. "Can this really predict from one photo?" was a recurring objection.
  • Navigation inconsistencies, missing links, and confusing CTAs damaged memorability and slowed returning users.
  • Results page had no "what next" ‚Äî users completed analysis but had no clear next action, creating a journey dead-end.
Outcome

Transformed Mindreader from a confusing AI experiment into a structured professional sales tool ‚Äî with a clearer value proposition on first load, a streamlined 3-step analysis flow, trust-first onboarding, and a unified design system enabling consistent implementation.
